NAME: tmortr
SCENARIO NAME: Trend of mortality reduction with time and technology
DEFINITION: Trend of mortality reduction with time and technology
Parameter Explanation: Time-related reduction in mortality, in portion per year (i.e., .01 represents 1 percent).  Although time-related, it is obviously meant to represent the affect of technological advance on life expectancy.  This parameter is global, and you will often prefer to use mortm to introduce scenarios around mortality and life expectancy, because that parameter is country/region specific.

NAME: tmortr2
SCENARIO NAME: Trend of mortality reduction with time and technology, LDC catch-up
DEFINITION: Trend of mortality reduction with time and technology, LDC catch-up
Parameter Explanation: Time-related reduction in mortality, in portion per year (i.e., .01 represents 1 percent). See and compare with tmortr; this represents catch-up in fertility reduction by poor countries using tech transfer.  Although time-related, it is obviously meant to represent the affect of technological advance on life expectancy.  This parameter is global, and you will often prefer to use mortm to introduce scenarios around mortality and life expectancy, because that parameter is country/region specific.

NAME: trademax
SCENARIO NAME: Trade, maximum as portion of tradable production base
DEFINITION: Trade, maximum as portion of tradable production base
Parameter Explanation: Maximum trade as a portion of tradable production base, expressed in decimal form. A value of 0.9 means 90%. Values can exceed 1.0 because some economies export and reexport more than they produce.

NAME: tradsratadd
SCENARIO NAME: Traditional/secular-rational values index addition
DEFINITION: Traditional/secular-rational index addition
Parameter Explanation: Additive factor to introduce a shift in Traditional/rational-secular indexindex for a region/country.  It increases or decreases the index value that the model calculates.  The normal value is zero.  See also and contrast with cultshmp, which is a cultural shift for the large cultural regions identified in the WVS project and which is calculated from data.

NAME: trucksconv
SCENARIO NAME: Truck sales, convergence to expected value
DEFINITION: Truck sales, convergence to expected value
Parameter Explanation: Convergence time for truck sales in years. This value determines the number of years over which all countries/regions will converge to the chosen function (as determined by the switch, vehfuncsw) for the computation of truck sales per year.  A value of 1000 would effectively turn off convergence, so that initial country-specific variations from the function would be maintained over time.  A value of 60 would lead to near convergence by the middle of the 21st century.  Very rapid convergence seems improbable in the face of fundamental country differences in infrastructure, land area, culture, etc.

NAME: truckstotm
SCENARIO NAME: Truck sales, total, multiplier
DEFINITION: Truck sales, total, multiplier
Parameter Explanation: Multiplier on total truck sales by country/region.  A value of 1.0 leaves total sales unchanged.  An increase over time to 2.0 would approximately double total sales relative to the base case (sales by type will not always change proportionately, because of differing relationships with total sales).

NAME: ttfrr
SCENARIO NAME: Trend reduction in TFR (total fertility rate)
DEFINITION: Trend reduction in TFR (total fertility rate)
Parameter Explanation: Time-related reduction in total fertility rate (TFR), in portion per year (i.e., .01 represents 1 percent).  Although time-related, it is obviously meant to represent the affect of technological and or cultural/value-based change in fertility rates.  This parameter is global, and you will often prefer to use tfrm to introduce scenarios around fertility rates, because that parameter is country/region specific.  This parameter represents, however, the historic phenomenon of "systemic shift" in fertility rates.

NAME: vehfuncsw
SCENARIO NAME: Vehicle function switch, across forecasting formulations
DEFINITION: Vehicle function switch, across forecasting formulations
Parameter Explanation: Vehicle function switch.  The switch controls which of several functions the model uses to compute car and truck sales.  The standard value for it is 4, which results in the use of a function for sales per capita dependent on GDP per capita at purchasing power, the WVS index for survival/self-expression values, and the WVS index for traditional/secular-rational values.

NAME: vehicflpcm
SCENARIO NAME: Vehicle fleet per capita, multiplier
DEFINITION: Vehicle fleet per capita, multiplier
Parameter Explanation: Multiplier on vehicles per capita by country/region.  A value of 1.0 leaves vehicles per capita unchanged.  An increase over time to 2.0 would double vehicles per capita relative to the base case.

NAME: wagnerc
SCENARIO NAME: Wagner's law coeficient; annual growth in govt expenditures
DEFINITION: Wagner's law coeficient; annual growth in govt expenditures
Parameter Explanation: Wagner's law coeficient; annual growth in govt expenditures.  Wagner's Law (from the late 1800s) said that government expenditures would continue to increase as a portion of GDP.  Although this effect must ultimately saturate (the model limits it), it has continued into the 21st century.  You can set a value in terms of annual percentage increase (or decrease) in government/GDP. Thus, 1 = 1% annual increase in the ratio.

NAME: waron
SCENARIO NAME: War switch to turn on war option (1=on; 0=off)
DEFINITION: War switch to turn on war option (1=on; 0=off)
Parameter Explanation: A switch that can be used to turn on or off the possibility of war.  A value of 0 turns off war and a value of 1 makes it possible.  It does not, however, make war certain - that will depend on calculations within each dyad of the probability of war and the conversion (via random processes) of such probabilities into actual conventional or nuclear war.

NAME: wastewaterportiontreated
SCENARIO NAME: wastewaterportiontreated
DEFINITION: Portion of wastewater that is treated
Parameter Explanation: This parameter determines the portion of treated waste water.

NAME: wastewatertreatedm
SCENARIO NAME: treated wastewater multiplier
DEFINITION: treated wastewater multiplier
Parameter Explanation: Multiplier on treated waster water.

NAME: wastewatportreatreusedm
SCENARIO NAME: Wastewater portion treated reused multiplier
DEFINITION: Portion of treated wastewater that is reused, multipliier
Parameter Explanation: Multiplier on the portion of treated waste water that is then re-used.

NAME: waterdesalinatedgr
SCENARIO NAME: waterdesalinatedgr
DEFINITION: Desalinated water initial growth rate
Parameter Explanation: Initial growth rate of desalinated water.

NAME: waterdesalinatedm
SCENARIO NAME: waterdesalinatedm
DEFINITION: Desalinated water multiplier
Parameter Explanation: Multiplier on the level of desalinated water.

NAME: waterfilteredm
SCENARIO NAME: Water source, percentage of people served with filtered, multiplier
DEFINITION: Water source, percentage served with filtered water, multiplier
Parameter Explanation: Multiplier for the percentage of people of a certain type of water source who are served with filtered water

NAME: waterhhcostlowershr
DISPLAY NAME: Water Services, Share of Services Using Lower-Cost Technology
SCENARIO NAME: Water Services, Share of Services Using Lower-Cost Service
DEFINITION: Infrastructure, water services, share of services using lower-cost service
Parameter Explanation: Infrastructure, water services, share of services using lower-cost service. Base case value is 50/50 when both lower and upper cost services are available

NAME: watertoyieldswitch
DISPLAY NAME: switch to allow water to constrain ag yield
SCENARIO NAME: switch to allow water to constrain ag yield
DEFINITION: switch to allow water to constrain ag yield
Parameter Explanation: Switch to allow water to constrain agricultural yields.

NAME: watpricetoylelas
DISPLAY NAME: elasticity from water price to irrigated land yield
SCENARIO NAME: elasticity from water price to irrigated land yield
DEFINITION: Elasticity from water price to irrigated land yield
Parameter Explanation: Elasticity that helps create a multiplier on yield by multiplying the ratio of change in water price relative to base water price and adding to 1.

NAME: watprid
DISPLAY NAME: water price responsiveness to change in stock/inventory levels
SCENARIO NAME: water price responsiveness to change in stock/inventory levels
DEFINITION: water price responsiveness to change in stock/inventory levels
Parameter Explanation: Responsiveness of water price to change in stock/inventory levels.

NAME: watprii
DISPLAY NAME: water price responsiveness to changes in stock level
SCENARIO NAME: water price responsiveness to stock/inventory levels
DEFINITION: water price responsiveness to stock/inventory levels
Parameter Explanation: Responsiveness of water price to stock/inventory levels.  watprii and watprid are a pair of adjustment parameters (not true elasticities), most of which normally have about a 1:2 ratio.  Significant changes in this parameter could destabilize model behavior.

NAME: watres
SCENARIO NAME: Water resources, renewable
DEFINITION: Water resources, renewable
Parameter Explanation: Renewable water resources, expressed in cubic kilometers. This parameter is now purely informational, because IFs does not have a dynamic water model that uses it to constrain water use.

SCENARIO NAME: Water and Sanitation 5 Category Switch

NAME: watsafenoconsetar
DISPLAY NAME: Safe Water, No Connection, Standard Error Target
SCENARIO NAME: Safe Water, No Connection, Standard Error Target
DEFINITION: Infrastructure, safe water, no connection, strandard error target
Parameter Explanation: Sets the number of Standard Errors to be targeted by the forecast (between -2 and 2), 0 turns off the targetting.

NAME: watsafenoconseyrtar

SCENARIO NAME: Years to Target Safe Water, no con, Std Error

NAME: watsafetrgtval

SCENARIO NAME: Safe Water Access Fixed Target Value

NAME: wmigrm
SCENARIO NAME: World migration rate multipler
DEFINITION: World migration rate multiplier
Parameter Explanation: World migration rate multiplier.  This is a very useful parameter for increasing or decreasing migration rates globally, because it applies to all rates rather than just to those for a particular country or region (for control by country/region see migrater).  A value of 1 implies no change, while higher values proportionately increase the underlying variable and lower values decrease it.  Like other multipliers, you should generally not change the value in the initial year because that would override empirical initial conditions; rather you should ramp up or down the multiplier value over time.

NAME: workageentry
SCENARIO NAME: Age of common entry into the work force
DEFINITION: Age of common entry into the work force
Parameter Explanation: Age of common entry into the work force, sets the entry to the labor force.

NAME: workageretire
SCENARIO NAME: Age of normal retirement
DEFINITION: Age of normal retirement
Parameter Explanation: Age of normal retirement, sets the exit of the labor force

NAME: workageretiresv
SCENARIO NAME: Age of retirement to compute savings rate
DEFINITION: Age of retirement to compute savings rate
Parameter Explanation: Age of retirement to compute savings rate, input for function to compute Savings rate needed, it allows to analyze Savings rate needed independently of changes in retirement age when using mixed scenarios.

NAME: wpally
SCENARIO NAME: World politics, reduction of dispute threat with alliance in dyad
DEFINITION: World politics, reduction of dispute threat with alliance in dyad
Parameter Explanation: World politics, reduction of dispute threat with alliance in dyad.  The value is in percent probability of a dispute.  That is, -0.1 would indicate that being in an alliance would reduce the probability of a dispute between two states by 0.1%, all else being equal.  Note that this results in a value added to or subtracted from other terms in the calculation of dispute probability (it is not used multiplicatively so as to change an otherwise calculated probability by x%).

NAME: wpcommun
SCENARIO NAME: World politics, response of dispute threat to global community level
DEFINITION: World politics, response of dispute threat to global community level
Parameter Explanation: War probability elasticity with global community.  This parameter and the underlying level of global community (GLOCOM) are not now being used in the calculation of threat.

NAME: wpcon
SCENARIO NAME: World politics, change in dispute threat with power concentration
DEFINITION: World politics, change in dispute threat with power concentration
Parameter Explanation: World politics, change in dispute threat with power concentration.  This value is used in a function as a multiplier on global power concentration among great powers (PCONGREAT), a variable which itself normally ranges from approximately 0.2 to 0.4.  The change in the result of the product from year to year provides an additive term that can be interpreted as an additive increase (or decrease) in the probability of disputes between two countries/regions.

NAME: wpconmax
SCENARIO NAME: World politics, maximum power concentration affecting dispute probability
DEFINITION: World politics, maximum power concentration affecting dispute probability
Parameter Explanation: World politics, maximum power concentration affecting dispute probability.  This parameter bounds the power concentration range within which change affects dispute probability.

NAME: wpconmin
SCENARIO NAME: World politics, minimum power concentration affecting dispute probability
DEFINITION: World politics, minimum power concentration affecting dispute probability
Parameter Explanation: World politics, minimum power concentration affecting dispute probability.  This parameter bounds the power concentration range within which change affects dispute probability.

NAME: wpconsq
SCENARIO NAME: World politics, change in dispute threat with change in power concentration
DEFINITION: World politics, change in dispute threat with change in power concentration
Parameter Explanation: World politics, change in dispute threat with the square of change in power concentration (see also wpcon).  This value is used in a function as a multiplier on the square of global power concentration among great powers (PCONGREAT), a variable which itself normally ranges from approximately 0.2 to 0.4.  The change in the result of the product of the parameter and the square of concentration from year to year provides an additive term that can be interpreted as an additive increase (or decrease) in the probability of disputes between two countries/regions.

NAME: wpdemdist
SCENARIO NAME: World politics, response of dispute threat to political distance
DEFINITION: World politics, response of dispute threat to political distance
Parameter Explanation: World politics, response of dispute threat to political distance.  The value is in percent probability of a dispute and is applied to the absolute value of the distance in democracy level between the states in a dyad.  That is, 0.01 would indicate that every point of additional distance on the underlying Polity scale would increase the probability of a dispute between two states by 0.01%, all else being equal.  Note that this results in a value added to or subtracted from other terms in the calculation of dispute probability (it is not used multiplicatively so as to change an otherwise calculated probability by x%).

NAME: wpdemmin
SCENARIO NAME: World politics, response of dispute threat to minimum democracy level in dyad
DEFINITION: World politics, response of dispute threat to minimum democracy level in dyad
Parameter Explanation: World politics, response of dispute threat to minimum democracy level in dyad.  The value is in percent probability of a dispute and is applied to the democracy level in the less democratic state in a dyad.  That is, -0.01 would indicate that every point of additional democracy on the underlying Polity scale would reduce the probability of a dispute between two states by 0.01%, all else being equal.  Note that this results in a value added to or subtracted from other terms in the calculation of dispute probability (it is not used multiplicatively so as to change an otherwise calculated probability by x%).

NAME: wpextinterv
SCENARIO NAME: World politics, external intervention switch (1=On, 0=Off)
DEFINITION: World politics, external intervention switch (1=On, 0=Off)
Parameter Explanation: External intervention forcing switch.  A value of 1 turns on the intervention in a country from another country (unspecified); it will affect internal conflict

NAME: wpgreat1
SCENARIO NAME: World politics, increment of dispute probability in dyad with one great power
DEFINITION: World politics, increment of dispute probability in dyad with one great power
Parameter Explanation: World politics, increment of dispute probability in dyad with one great power.  The value is in percent probability of a dispute and is applied when at least one member of the dyad is a great power (see wpgreatthesh and wpgreatlev for definitions of great power).  That is, 0.7 would indicate that the existence of one great power would increase the probability of a dispute between two states by 0.7%, all else being equal.  Note that this results in a value added to or subtracted from other terms in the calculation of dispute probability (it is not used multiplicatively so as to change an otherwise calculated probability by x%).

NAME: wpgreat2
SCENARIO NAME: World politics, increment of dispute probability in dyad with two great powers
DEFINITION: World politics, increment of dispute probability in dyad with two great powers
Parameter Explanation: World politics, increment of dispute probability in dyad with two great powers.  The value is in percent probability of a dispute and is applied when at both members of the dyad are great powers (see wpgreatthesh and wpgreatlev for definitions of great power).  That is, 2.0 would indicate that the existence of two great powers would increase the probability of a dispute between two states by 2.0%, all else being equal.   Note that this results in a value added to or subtracted from other terms in the calculation of dispute probability (it is not used multiplicatively so as to change an otherwise calculated probability by x%).  This addition would be on top of the increment already added for the presence of one great power in a dyad (see wpgreat1).

NAME: wpgreatlev
SCENARIO NAME: World politics, systemic power share required for full great power status
DEFINITION: World politics, systemic power share required for full great power status
Parameter Explanation: World politics, systemic power share required for full great power status.  The value is in percent of systemic power.  Thus 5.0 would indicate that a state reached the status of full great power when its share of total global power reached 5.0%.  See also the threshold for beginning to be a great power, wpgreatlev.

NAME: wpgreatthresh
SCENARIO NAME: World politics, systemic power share for threshhold great power status
DEFINITION: World politics, systemic power share for threshhold great power status
Parameter Explanation: World politics, systemic power share for threshhold great power status.  The value is in percent of systemic power.  Thus 2.0 would indicate that a state was just beginning to be a great power when its share of total global power reached 2.0%. See also the level to be a full great power, wpgreatlev.

NAME: wpindsw
SCENARIO NAME: Character of Bilateral State Interaction Score switch
DEFINITION: Character of Bilateral State Interaction Score switch
Parameter Explanation: A switch that can be used to turn on or off the calculations of Character of Bilateral State Interaction Score.  A value of 0 turns it off and a value greater than 0 turns it on.  1 is used to save threat, 2 is used to save Liberal Index, 3 is used to save Realist Index and 4 is used to save the COI.

NAME: wpmilthr
SCENARIO NAME: World politics, reactivity of military spending to changes in threat
DEFINITION: World politics, reactivity of military spending to changes in threat

NAME: wppowhhsw
SCENARIO NAME: World politics, power index switch (1 means using HH index)
DEFINITION: World politics, power index switch (1 means using HH index)
Parameter Explanation: World politics, power index switch, 1 means using POWERHH index to drive forward linkages, instead of the defaul POWER index.

NAME: wppowtran1
SCENARIO NAME: World politics, ratio of power where transition begins
DEFINITION: World politics, ratio of power where transition begins
Parameter Explanation: World politics, ratio of power where transition begins.  If the value were 0.7 it would indicate that when the weaker power in a dyad reached 0.7 (or 70%) of the power of the stronger, a power transition would begin.

NAME: wppowtran2
SCENARIO NAME: World politics, increase in dispute probability with 10% greater power parity
DEFINITION: World politics, increase in dispute probability with 10% greater power parity
Parameter Explanation: World politics, increase in dispute probability with 10% greater power parity.  The value is in percent. Thus 0.05 would indicate that the probability of a dispute between two states would rise by 0.05% for each 10% reduction in the power differential between them (or a reduction of 0.1 on a ratio scale).  See also the threshold for the beginning of a power transition, wppowtran1.  Note that this results in a value added to or subtracted from other terms in the calculation of dispute probability (it is not used multiplicatively so as to change an otherwise calculated probability by x%).

NAME: wpsysgr
SCENARIO NAME: World politics, change in dispute probability with global economic growth
DEFINITION: World politics, change in dispute probability with global economic growth
Parameter Explanation: World politics, change in dispute probability with global economic growth. The value is in percent. Thus 0.1 would indicate that the probability of a dispute between two states would rise by 0.1% for each percentage point increase in global economic growth relative to the long-term average.  Note that this results in a value added to or subtracted from other terms in the calculation of dispute probability (it is not used multiplicatively so as to change an otherwise calculated probability by x%).

NAME: wpterdisp
SCENARIO NAME: World politics, increase in militarized dispute prob with territorial dispute
DEFINITION: World politics, increase in militarized dispute prob with territorial dispute
Parameter Explanation: World politics, increase in militarized dispute probability with territorial dispute. The value is in percent. Thus 5.0 would indicate that the probability of a dispute between two states would rise by 5.0% if they have a territorial dispute outstanding, relative to the same pair without such a dispute.  Note that this results in a value added to or subtracted from other terms in the calculation of dispute probability (it is not used multiplicatively so as to change an otherwise calculated probability by x%).

NAME: wpthrconv
SCENARIO NAME: World politics, convergence time to predicted underlying threat levels
DEFINITION: World politics, convergence time to predicted underlying threat levels
Parameter Explanation: World politics, convergence time to predicted underlying threat levels.  Very often initial data values for countries, such as dyadic conflict in this case, will differ a little or much from values predicted by broader empirical analysis across states (and possibly across time).  It is never certain whether such differences involve data errors or idiosyncratic factors.  A paradigmatic assumption of IFs is that, over time, values for such variables will very often gradually converge to the values predicted by the function and the initial country- or dyad-specific "shift" should disappear.  A high value such as 10000 will effectively turn off the convergence process altogether, while a low value such as 10 will make it very rapid.  It is possible to set this parameter to 1, thereby replacing the empirical value by predicted values already in the first year and then every year thereafter.

NAME: wpthrwar
SCENARIO NAME: World politics, portion of all disputes that escalate to wars
DEFINITION: World politics, portion of all disputes that escalate to wars
Parameter Explanation: World politics, portion of all disputes that escalate to wars.  The value is in percent. Thus 3.3 would indicate that the probability of a war between two states would be 3.3% if they experienced a militarized international dispute (or 0.33% if the probability of a dispute were 10%).  This parameter is not now being use to generate wars from disputes.

NAME: wptrade
SCENARIO NAME: World politics, change in dispute threat with systemic trade
DEFINITION: World politics, change in dispute threat with systemic trade
Parameter Explanation: World politics, change in dispute threat with systemic trade.  The value is in percent. Thus -0.01% would indicate that the probability of a dispute between two states would fall by 0.01% for every percentage increase in world trade as a percent of global GDP.  Note that this results in a value added to or subtracted from other terms in the calculation of dispute probability (it is not used multiplicatively so as to change an otherwise calculated probability by x%).

NAME: wpwghtpow
SCENARIO NAME: World politics, contribution of various components to power index
DEFINITION: World politics, contribution of various components to power index
Parameter Explanation: World politics, contribution of various components to power index.  This is a vector across all the allowable contributing variables in the calculation of state power.  Values of "1" turn on the contribution of a variable and values of "0" turn off the contribution.

NAME: wtempadd
SCENARIO NAME: Addition to calculated global temperature
DEFINITION: Addition to calculated global temperature
Parameter Explanation: Parameter that sets the additive factor to the calculated global temperature.

NAME: wvsagesw
SCENARIO NAME: World Value Survey aging function switch
DEFINITION: World Value Survey aging function switch
Parameter Explanation: Switch for World Value Survets aging.  The parameter controls the dynamics associated with the value orientation of cohorts in the model.  The standard value for it is 2, which results in the "aging" of value orientations.  That is, value orientation is calculated from GDP per capita only for the youngest cohort; all others carry their orientation forward in time.  Any other value for wvsagesw (the WVS aging switch) will result in use of the cohort-specific functions with GDP per capita.

NAME: xarmsadd
SCENARIO NAME: Arms exports additive factor
DEFINITION: Arms exports additive factor
Parameter Explanation: Arms exports additive factor.  A value of 0 implies no change, while positive values increase the underlying value and negative values decrease it.  Like other additive factors, you should generally not change the value in the initial year because that would override empirical initial conditions; rather you should ramp up or down the parameter value over time.

NAME: xarmsm
SCENARIO NAME: Arms exports multiplier
DEFINITION: Arms exports multiplier
Parameter Explanation: Arms exports multiplier.  A value of 1 implies no change, while higher values proportionately increase the underlying value and lower values decrease it.  Like other multipliers, you should generally not change the value in the initial year because that would override empirical initial conditions; rather you should ramp up or down the multiplier value over time.

NAME: xcadjsw
SCENARIO NAME: Export Capacity Adjustment Switch
DEFINITION: Export Capacity Adjustment Switch
Parameter Explanation: Switch for export capacity adjustment. When the switch is ON, we adjust Exports based on changes in imports from main partners.

NAME: ylexp
SCENARIO NAME: Yields (agricultural), exponent controlling saturation speed
DEFINITION: Yields (agricultural), exponent controlling saturation speed
Parameter Explanation: Agricultural yields' exponent controlling saturation speed represents a slowdown in the rate of yield increases as they approach the maximum (ylmax), ensuring a gradual, asymptotic approach to the yield ceiling.

NAME: ylm
SCENARIO NAME: Yields (agricultural), multiplier
DEFINITION: Yields (agricultural), multiplier
Parameter Explanation: Multiplier on agricultureal yields, by region. It is used to represent potential yield changes due to technological or environmental factors. The value is typically adjusted over time rather than in the initial year. For example, a value of 1 represents no change, 1.25 represents a 25 percent increase and .75 represents a 25 percent decrease.

NAME: ylmaxgr
SCENARIO NAME: Yields (agricultural), maximum annual growth
DEFINITION: Yields (agricultural), maximum annual growth
Parameter Explanation: Parameter that roughly controls the the maximum increase in agricultural yields (.05 would be 5% annually).  It is phased downward at the hhighest values of current yields.
